returnType: The CUME_DIST function returns a numeric value.
description: The Oracle/PLSQL CUME_DIST function returns the cumulative distribution of a value in a group of values. The CUME_DIST function will return a value that is >0 and <=1. The CUME_DIST function can be used two ways - as an Aggregate function or as an Analytic function.
sample:
select CUME_DIST(1000, 500) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY salary, bonus)
from employees;
